# Lesson 06

# Prepare the Camp

## Why this lesson exists

Explorers do not begin an expedition the moment they arrive at the trailhead.

They stop.

They check their equipment.

They review the map.

They make sure everyone is ready.

Only then do they take the first step.

Your Lab deserves the same care.

This lesson brings together everything you have prepared so far and confirms that your Lab is ready for its first real Mission.

---

## The Question

Is my Lab truly ready for exploration?

---

## Learning Objectives

By the end of this lesson you should be able to:

- verify that your preparation is complete;
- confirm that your Lab satisfies its documented requirements;
- ensure your recovery strategy can be trusted;
- confirm that your documentation is complete enough to support future Adventures;
- begin the Mission with confidence.

---

## Understand

Preparation is often invisible.

Nobody notices the checklist that prevented a mistake.

Nobody celebrates the backup that was never needed.

Nobody applauds the documentation that answered tomorrow's question.

Good preparation rarely attracts attention.

It quietly makes everything else possible.

Professional engineers know that confidence comes from preparation—not from luck.

---

## Practice

Review everything you created during this Adventure.

### Explorer Journal

- Have I adopted an explorer's mindset?
- Do I understand why this Lab exists?

### Lab Requirements Profile

- Are my requirements complete?
- Have I prioritised them?

### Toolkit Decision Record

- Can I explain every major decision?
- Are the trade-offs documented?

### Recovery Strategy

- Have I tested the recovery process?
- Do I trust it?

### Documentation Guide

- Would Future Me understand my work?
- Is everything stored where it belongs?

---

## Mission Readiness Checklist

Before beginning the Mission, confirm:

- [ ] My Lab requirements are complete.
- [ ] My toolkit has been selected.
- [ ] My recovery strategy has been documented.
- [ ] My documentation guide is ready.
- [ ] My host system is prepared.
- [ ] I understand the purpose of every tool I am about to install.
- [ ] I know how I will recover if something goes wrong.
- [ ] I am ready to build.

---

## Build Your Mission Plan

Create a document called:

```text
Mission Plan
```

Include:

```text
Mission Objective

Starting Point

Required Tools

Implementation Order

Validation Steps

Rollback Plan

Success Criteria

Next Actions
```

This document becomes your roadmap during the Mission.

---

## Prepare

There is nothing left to plan.

There is nothing left to design.

There is nothing left to decide.

Everything from this point forward happens inside your Lab.

The Mission begins.

---

## Campfire

Take one last moment before you begin.

- Which part of my preparation gives me the most confidence?
- Which uncertainty still remains?
- What am I most excited to build?
- What do I expect to be the biggest challenge?
- If Future Me could give me one piece of advice before I begin, what might it be?

